						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Kōṉēriṉmaikoṇḍāṉ Vīrarājēndra: Year 15+1+1 = 1223-24 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is incomplete and damaged. It records a gift of paddy, made by the king, to a private individual named Kaṇḍaṉ Adiyaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vaḷaviṉāṉ Uḍaiyān, in the village of Kallāpuram <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vīraśōḻanallūr, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> of the god Vīrachōḻīśvaramuḍaiyār. It appears that this donee was enjoined to render certain services to the god Vīrachōḻīśvaramuḍaiyār.</p>						

						</summary>
